						<summary>

						<p>On the west face of the north pillar in the rock-cut shrine in the Mēlaikōyil temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 15 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju tuḷaippoṉ</hi> by Kōdaṇḍarāmaṉ, son of Śrī Pirāntakar <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śōḻa-Perumāṉaḍigaḷ for burning two perpetual lamps.</p>						

						</summary>
